An Ikorodu Chief Magistrates’ Court on Monday remanded in prison an unemployed man, Emmanuel Mesaiybe, 35, for allegedly sexually assaulting a seven-year-old girl. He was charged with indecent assault before Chief Magistrate Fimisola Azeez. His plea was not taken.  The Chief Magistrate ordered that the case file be sent to Lagos State Director of Public Prosecution (DPP) for advice. She adjourned till July 25. Earlier, prosecuting Sergeant John Iberedem told the court that the defendant committed the offence on May 30, at Lanre Akinjobi Street, Butterfly Estate, Owutu in Ikorodu. The prosecutor alleged that the defendant unlawfully had carnal knowledge of the minor.